      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MORE WANTED (9) hasn't been far off some handy rivals of late, coming from this barrier and chasing a subsequent Group 1 placegetter when fourth at this circuit and distance last start. If things go his way he is up to winning a race like this. ALRIGHTY (5) hasn't raced since February but has won two of three previous fresh attempts and a trial win suggests he'll be ready to go again. KEAYANG KURKI (6) was far from disgraced in the resuming fourth after racing three wide without cover. Fitter and with better luck she can make an impact. MUSKEE (3) has been coming from the second line of late but did score back-to-back wins from this row here in May so is better served tonight. The ace draw could see NAKEDTRUTH (1) competitive again.",
